rulesText: FREEZE — Exert chosen opposing character.
flavorText: Recreated by magical ink, Elsa found herself in an entirely new world. Fortunately, ice works the same way everywhere.

fullName: Cruella de vil - Miserable as Usual
rulesText: YOU'LL BE SORRY! When this character is challenged and banished, you may return chosen character to their player's hand.
flavorText: When she stops by, misery is company.

rulesText: DRAGON FIRE When you play this character, you may banish chosen character.
flavorText: The ninth Rule of Villainy: When all else fails, turn into a dragon.

rulesText: FEED THE POOR When you play this character, if an opponent has more cards in their hand than you, draw a card. GOOD SHOT During your turn, this character gains Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)
flavorText: We never rob. We just sort of borrow a bit from those who can afford it.

rulesText: Challenger +2 (While challenging, this character gets +2.)
flavorText: He loves to make light of a foe’s predicament.

rulesText: GET A CLUE When you play this character, you may put the top card of your deck into your inkwell facedown and exerted.
flavorText: Wherever the seaweed had come from, Mickey was sure of one thing: something fishy was going on.

rulesText: Support (Whenever this character quests, you may add their to another chosen character's this turn.)
flavorText: Sometimes, our strengths lie beneath the surface. Far beneath, in some cases.... —Moana

rulesText: YOU'RE EXCUSED Whenever this character quests, look at the top card of your deck. Put it on either the top or the bottom of your deck.
flavorText: When I want your opinion, I will give it to you!

rulesText: Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.) ALL FOR ONE Your other Musketeer characters get +1.

Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.) AND TWO FOR TEA! When you play this character, you may remove up to 2 damage from each of your Musketeer characters.
flavorText: En gawrsh!

rulesText: Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.) STAY ALERT! During your turn, your Musketeer characters gain Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)
HAVE COURAGE When you play this character, you may draw a card, then choose and discard a card.
flavorText: She's always had the heart of a champion—now she'll have the skills, too.

rulesText: Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.) SQUEAK Whenever you play a Floodborn character, each opponent chooses and discards a card.
flavorText: There’s a lot of nuance to squirrel. —Kronk

rulesText: Shift 2 (You may pay 2 to play this on top of one of your characters named Minnie Mouse.) Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.) UNDERSEA ADVENTURE Whenever you play a second action in a turn, this character gets +2 this turn.
SKIRMISH — Deal 1 damage to chosen character.
flavorText: Capable? You don’t know the half of it. —Little John

rulesText: BIENVENUE DANS MA MAISON Lorsque ce personnage est envoyé à l'aventure, le prochain personnage que vous jouez durant ce tour vous coûte 3 de moins.
flavorText: Entrez, il y a beaucoup de choses à découvrir.

rulesText: Offensif +3 (Lorsqu'il défie, ce personnage gagne +3.)
flavorText: Le pouvoir de la glace n'arrêtera peut-être pas l'inondation, mais il aidera à protéger Lorcana.

rulesText: Alter 6 (Vous pouvez payer 6 pour jouer ce personnage sur l'un de vos personnages Génie.) Insaisissable (Seuls les personnages avec Insaisissable peuvent défier ce personnage.) POUVOIR COSMIQUE PHÉNOMÉNAL! Lorsque ce personnage est envoyé à l'aventure, vous pouvez jouer gratuitement une carte action coûtant 5 ou moins.

flavorText: Vous allez voir l'expérience 626 passer à l'action. Il sera attiré vers les grandes villes où il bouchera les égouts, inversera les panneaux de signalisation et volera toutes les chaussures gauches. — Jumba Jookiba
Elle n'avait pas été invitée… et n'avait nullement besoin qu'on l'annonce.
Lorsque les dieux t'offrent un bateau, tu l'acceptes… mais tu n'es pas obligé de garder son propriétaire.

rulesText: Reckless (This character can't quest and must challenge each turn if able.)
flavorText: It’s not arrogance when you really <are> the best.

rulesText: SKYSURFING When you play this character, you may return chosen opposing character with 2 or less to their player's hand.
flavorText: It’s been fun, guys, but I got to be going. Yahoooo!

rulesText: LOOK ALIVE, YOU SWABS! Characters gain Rush while here. (They can challenge the turn they're played.) ALL HANDS ON DECK! Your Pirate characters may move here for free.
(A character with cost 4 or more can to play this song for free.) Look at the top 2 cards of your deck. Put one into your hand and the other into your inkwell facedown and exerted.
CHART YOUR OWN COURSE For each location you have in play, this character gains Resist +1 and gets +1. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)
flavorText: I was never much good at games. Always hated to lose.

rulesText: Shift 4 (You may pay 4 to play this on top of one of your characters named Stitch.) ADORING FANS Whenever you play a character with cost 2 or less, you may exert them to draw a card.
flavorText: The best part about a beachside concert is that there’s always room for one more.

rulesText: Shift 3 (You may pay 3 to play this on top of one of your characters named Rapunzel.) LET YOUR POWER SHINE Whenever you remove 1 or more damage from one of your characters, you may draw a card.
TELLING LIES When you play this character, you may exert chosen opposing character.
flavorText: A lie keeps growing and growing until it’s as plain as the nose on your face. —Blue Fairy

rulesText: (A character with cost 4 or more can to sing this song for free.) Your characters gain Resist +2 until the start of your next turn. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 2.)
